Former Speaker Dimeji Bankole has picked the presidential expression of interest and nomination forms of the All Progressives Congress (APC). Former Zamfara Governor Mahmuda Aliyu Shinkafi led the delegation that bought the forms at the cost of N100m on behalf of Bankole on Friday.   PHOTOS: Tinubu, Osinbajo, Fayemi, others at Southwest APC…     UPDATED: Former Zamfara Gov Yerima joins presidential race     Nigeria’s crude oil reserves increase to 37.04bb   The Nation gathered Bankole decided to join the presidential race after consulting with stakeholders across the country. Bankole, who was the 2019 governorship candidate of Action Democratic Party (ADP) in Ogun State, officially registered as a member of the APC in March 2021.